1. DEFINITIONS

"Runner" means the compiled Bitbybit Runner JavaScript bundle files
(bitbybit-runner-babylonjs.js, bitbybit-runner-threejs.js,
bitbybit-runner-playcanvas.js, bitbybit-runner-core.js, and their
respective "lite" variants), the associated Web Worker files, WebAssembly
binaries, and any supporting assets distributed alongside them.

"Open-Source Components" means the portions of the Runner derived from
third-party open-source projects, as listed in the NOTICE file. These
components are governed by their respective licenses.

"Proprietary Components" means all portions of the Runner that are not
Open-Source Components, including but not limited to proprietary algorithms,
orchestration logic, and integration code authored by MB "Bit by bit
developers".

"CDN Assets" means the Runner files and supporting assets (Web Workers,
WebAssembly binaries, fonts) hosted on the Bitbybit CDN at
git-cdn.bitbybit.dev or any successor URL.

