4. OPEN-SOURCE COMPONENTS

The Runner incorporates Open-Source Components that are licensed under their
respective open-source licenses (including MIT, LGPL v2.1, and Apache 2.0).
Nothing in this License restricts your rights under those open-source
licenses with respect to those components. A complete list of Open-Source
Components and their licenses is provided in the accompanying NOTICE file.

LGPL Compliance: The OpenCASCADE Technology (OCCT) component is licensed
under LGPL v2.1 and is loaded as a separate, dynamically-linked Web Worker
at runtime. You may replace the OCCT Web Worker and WebAssembly binary with
your own LGPL-compliant build by using the cdnUrl configuration option or
by self-hosting modified worker files. See the Bitbybit documentation for
the worker interface specification.

If you wish to modify or use the Open-Source Components independently of
the Runner, their source code is available at:
https://github.com/bitbybit-dev/bitbybit

